content:
Route Data to Objects in Bring Your Own Channel

Use parameters, parameter mappings, and flows to route customer data to Salesforce objects. This data gives agents more context for who they’re messaging with.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience

Parameters establish the data that you want to collect from your customer. Parameter mapping connects a parameter to a flow variable, sending the collected data into a flow. The Omni-Channel Flow takes the flow variable and sends it to an object.

For example, create a Support Reason dropdown menu, and then route the customer’s input to the Messaging Session object using parameters, parameter mappings, and flows.
title: Routing Customer Data in Bring Your Own Channel
